        "desc": "The heart of Gravenhurst's waterfront and one of Muskoka's most iconic attractions. Step aboard the RMS Segwun - the oldest operating steamship in North America, built in 1887 - for a Lake Muskoka cruise. The Muskoka Wharf complex includes waterfront restaurants, shops, boutique hotels, and a marina. The Steamships & Heritage Discovery Centre tells the story of Muskoka's steamship era. Summer evenings bring the Music on the Barge concert series. A perfect two-hour stop in Gravenhurst.",
